    "(8)This dotted line satisfies the following local relations for any x ∈ Ob C and any X ∈ Ob Z(C) ([36, Corollary 3.5], [39, Lemma 2.2]):=, =, =(9)on embedded disks and annuli in any decorated surface.",
    "These are called the normalization, projector, and cloaking properties of the dotted line.",
    "GluingLet Σ be a decorated surface and let N, M ⊂ ∂Σ be two disjoint decorated submanifolds of the boundary of Σ.",
    "We say N can be glued to M if N ≃ M as decorated 1-manifolds.",
    "If this is the case then there is an orientation reversing homeomorphism ψ: N → M which maps marked boundary points to marked boundary points."
